r_title                    = Chairperson<!-- Mayor, Municipal Commissioner etc. -->\n| leader_name                     = Sindhu Singh<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0938\u0940\u0935\u093e\u0928 \u0928\u0917\u0930 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u0937\u0926 \u0915\u0940 \u091a\u0947\u092f\u0930\u092e\u0948\u0928 \u092c\u0928\u0940 \u0938\u093f\u0902\u0927\u0942 \u0926\u0947\u0935\u0940 |url=https://m.livehindustan.com/bihar/siwan/story-sindhu-devi-the-chairman-of-the-city-of-siwan-1131004.html |website=[[Hindustan (newspaper)|Hindustan]] |accessdate=5 May 2019 |language=hindi}}</ref>\n| leader_title2                   = Deputy chairman\n| leader_name2                    = Bablu Shah\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=\"smc\"/>\n| area_rank                       = 53rd\n| area_total_km2                  = 13.05\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 72\n| population_total                = 135066\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = 18th\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = <ref name=\"Census2011Gov\"/>\n| demographics_type1              = [[Language]]\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]<ref name=\"langoff\">{{cite web|title=52nd REPORT OF THE COMMISSIONER FOR LINGUISTIC MINORITIES IN INDIA|url=http://nclm.nic.in/shared/linkimages/NCLM52ndReport.pdf|website=nclm.nic.in|publisher=[[Ministry of Minority Affairs]]|accessdate=9 March 2019|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525141614/http://nclm.nic.in/shared/linkimages/NCLM52ndReport.pdf|archivedate=25 May 2017}}</ref>\n| demographics1_title2            = Additional&nbsp;official\n| demographics1_info2             = [[Urdu]]<ref name=\"langoff\"/>\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = Pin Code<!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] -->\n| postal_code                     = 841226-841227\n| registration_plate              = BR-29\n| blank1_name_sec1                = [[Lok Sabha]] constituency\n| blank1_info_sec1                = [[Siwan (Lok Sabha constituency)|Siwan]]\n| blank2_name_sec1                = [[Vidhan Sabha]] constituency\n| blank2_info_sec1                = [[Siwan (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Siwan]]\n| website                         = https://siwan.nic.in/\n| iso_code                        = [[ISO 3166-2:IN|IN-BR]]\n| footnotes                       = \n| blank_name                      = [[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|Climate]]\n| blank_info                      = [[Humid subtropical climate|Cwa]]\n| official_name                   = \n| Siwan News                      = https://www.siwanonline.com\n}}\n'''Siwan''' is a city and [[nagar parishad]] in the Indian state of [[Bihar]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://siwan.nic.in/public-utility-category/municipality/ |title=Municipalities of Siwan district |date= |website=siwan.nic.in |publisher= |access-date=22 April 2019}}</ref> It is the administrative headquarters of [[Siwan district]] and one of the urban settlements out of three in the district. It is located close to [[Uttar Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.siwanonline.com/category/siwan-news-in-hindi/ |title=Siwan News |date= |publisher=www.siwanonline.com |accessdate=14 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe Siwan Municipal Council (SMC) was established in 1924.<ref name=\"smc\">{{cite web |url= http://urban.bih.nic.in/Docs/CDP/CDP-Siwan.pdf |title=City Development Plan for Siwan |date= |website=www.urban.bih.nic.in |publisher= |access-date=24 June 2018}}</ref> It was the subdivisional headquarter of Siwan subdivision and Siwan subdivision was a subdivision of old [[Saran district]]. \n\n==Geography and climate==\nSiwan city is located at coordinates {{Coord|26.22|N|84.36|E|}} Latitude and longitude. It has an average elevation of {{convert|72|m|ft}}.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.latlong.net/place/siwan-bihar-india-6984.html |title=Siwan, Bihar, India |date= |website= www.latlong.net |publisher= |access-date=19 June 2018}}</ref> Daha River, which is a small river, which floods in rainy season pass through the west of the town. The river dries up during summer. Daha river is also the most polluted river of Siwan district.\n\nThe weather of Siwan is mild and generally warm and temperate. This climate is considered to be Cwa according to the K\u00f6ppen-Geiger climate classification.<ref name= \"climate\"/>\n\n{{Weather box\n| width = auto\n| location = Siwan (1982-2012)\n| metric first = Y\n| single line = Y\n| open = yes\n| Jan high C = 23.1\n| Feb high C = 26.1\n| Mar high C = 32.4\n| Apr high C = 36.2\n| May high C = 38.6\n| Jun high C = 36.2\n| Jul high C = 32.8\n| Aug high C = 32.3\n| Sep high C = 32.\n| Oct high C = 31.8\n| Nov high C = 28.7\n| Dec high C = 24.7\n| year high C = \n\n|Jan mean C = 16.4\n|Feb mean C = 18.9\n|Mar mean C = 24.5\n|Apr mean C = 28.9\n|May mean C = 32\n|Jun mean C = 31.4\n|Jul mean C = 29.4\n|Aug mean C = 29.2\n|Sep mean C = 28.7\n|Oct mean C = 26.7\n|Nov mean C = 21.6\n|Dec mean C = 17.6\n|year mean C = \n\n| Jan low C = 9.8\n| Feb low C = 11.8\n| Mar low C = 16.7\n| Apr low C = 21.7\n| May low C = 25.5\n| Jun low C = 26.6\n| Jul low C = 26\n| Aug low C = 26.2\n| Sep low C = 25.5\n| Oct low C = 21.7\n| Nov low C = 14.5\n| Dec low C = 10.5\n| year low C = \n| Jan precipitation mm = 21\n| Feb precipitation mm = 7\n| Mar precipitation mm = 11\n| Apr precipitation mm = 7\n| May precipitation mm = 25\n| Jun precipitation mm = 164\n| Jul precipitation mm = 257\n| Aug precipitation mm = 316\n| Sep precipitation mm = 192\n| Oct precipitation mm = 54\n| Nov precipitation mm = 6\n| Dec precipitation mm = 2\n| year precipitation mm = \n| source 1 = '''Climate-data.org'''<ref name= \"climate\" >{{cite web\n| url = https://en.climate-data.org/location/52314/\n| title = Climate:Siwan\n| accessdate = 19 June 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of [[2011 Indian Census]], Siwan had a total population of 135,066, of which 70,756 were males and 64,310 were females. Population within the age group of 0 to 6 years was 18,282. The total number of literates in Siwan was 92,967, which constituted 68.8% of the population with male literacy of 73.6% and female literacy of 63.6%. The effective literacy rate of 7+ population of Siwan was 79.6%, of which male literacy rate was 85.2% and female literacy rate was 73.5%. The [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes]] population was 8,244 and 1,514 respectively. Siwan had 21223 households in 2011.<ref name=\"Census2011Gov\">{{cite web |title=Census of India: Siwan |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=262233 |website=www.censusindia.gov.in |accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{As of|2001}} India [[census]], Siwan had a population of 108,172 of which 57,223 were male and 50,949 female.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=16 June 2004|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns (Provisional)|accessdate=1 November 2008|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref>\n\n==Transport==\n[[National Highway 531 (India)|NH-531]] connects Siwan to [[Gopalganj, Bihar|Gopalganj]] and [[Chhapra]]. NH-531 meets to [[National Highway 27 (India)| NH-27]] at [[Gopalganj district, India|Gopalganj]]. Which is second longest road in India. [[List of state highways in Bihar |Bihar State Highway-47]] connects [[Barharia]], [[Mairwa]] and [[Guthani]] to Siwan. State Highway-73 and 89 also connects Siwan to nearest town and villages.\n\nThere is a [[Siwan Junction railway station]] in Siwan which connects to major cities of India. \n\nThere is no airports in Siwan. [[Jay Prakash Narayan Airport]] which is situated in [[Patna]], is the nearest airport to Siwan.\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Rajendra Prasad]], first president of India\n* [[Natwarlal]], noted fraudster\n* [[Bishwanath_Singh | Bishwanath Singh]], Free style wrestler (Asian and Commonwealth Games Silver Medalist)\n* [[Apoorvanand]], professor in Delhi University\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of cities in Bihar]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Blocks of Siwan district}}\n{{Saran Division}}\n{{Bihar-geo-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Siwan district]]\n[[Category:Siwan district]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|City in Bihar, India}}\n{{For|disambiguation|Siwan (disambiguation)}}\n{{refimprove|date=September 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n<!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Indian cities]] for details -->{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Siwan\n| other_name                      = <!-- Please do not add any Indic script in this infobox, per WP:INDICSCRIPT policy. -->\n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = City \n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Bihar#India#Asia\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Bihar, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|26.22|N|84.36|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Bihar]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Siwan district|Siwan]]\n| subdivision_type3            